            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_SENTRY_1_DESCRIPTION</LocID>         <Text>A defensive sentry turret that automatically fires at hostile units once per round.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_SENTRY_2_DESCRIPTION</LocID>         <Text>A stronger defensive sentry turret that automatically fires at hostile units once per round.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_SENTRY_3_DESCRIPTION</LocID>         <Text>A strong defensive sentry turret with manual control mode.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_SENTRY_BASE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>      <Text>The sentry has a proximity detector that activates it when a hostile unit gets close. It then automatically fires once per round.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>


            <!--Unit description-->
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_SPACESLUG_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                           <Text>Surprisingly intelligent and agile creatures that will probably replace the man's best friends. Poor monkeys, let's hope that they don't take that personally and won't start an uprising or something.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_SPIDER_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                              <Text>These jumping spiders are large enough to make even New Sydney colonists regret their decision to leave Earth. They also have a nasty habit of weaving large nests near bio farms and feeding off their waste. </Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_NIGHT_SPIDER_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                        <Text>Please note that military-grade insecticides make these spiders even stronger and more furious. Furthermore, imagine that there are flies of appropriate size. No more trips outside the colony walls. Never again! </Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_ROBOZOMBIE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                          <Text>First manufactured by a nameless castaway stranded in the wasteland. Maybe he wanted protection or just something to keep him company. Anyway, this "robozombie" became a popular security detail in all remote sectors.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_GENERIC_BADGER_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                      <Text>No one knows what their purpose is or what they do with the resources thay collect and take underground. One thing is crystal clear though. Those who dare to follow them never return.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_CRYSTAL_LIZARD_DAY_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                  <Text>The very crystals that allow them to shoot beams of energy will not stop growing once the lizards reach their adult size. Eventually, the poor sun-loving lizards are ripped from within. Natural evolution? I don't think so. </Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_CRYSTAL_LIZARD_NIGHT_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                <Text>Without the sun recharging their crystals, they can't shoot beams of energy anymore. Although their body is reinforced with the retracted crystals, all hunters unanimously agree that prey that does not shoot back is much easier to hunt.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_UNCORRUPTED_BEHOLDER_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                <Text>Don't be fooled by the fluffy fur. Underneath, Baloos are all muscles. If you're not a Steve Irwin type of badass, shaving a Baloo might be a really bad idea. </Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_GENERIC_TURRET_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                      <Text>Heavy autonomous turrets made by UNSS. Thanks to large caliber ammunition these models are capable of putting down even big pests like Sovereign fleets elite Thundermechs. </Text></GameDBLocalizedString>

            <!--Unit abilities-->
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_VEHICLE_SHIELD_INFO_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                 <Text><![CDATA[Protects your army from <color=SOTS_COLOR_GOLD>ranged attacks</color>.]]></Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_CRYSTAL_LIZARD_DAY_INFO_DESCRIPTION</LocID>             <Text>Has a ranged attack.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_CRYSTAL_LIZARD_DAY_DESERT_INFO_DESCRIPTION</LocID>      <Text>Shots are always precise.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
            <GameDBLocalizedString>         <LocID>UNIT_NEUTRAL_RADIANT_BADGER_INFO_DESCRIPTION</LocID>                 <Text>Has a ranged attack.</Text></GameDBLocalizedString>
